    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-24T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="210"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d210">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/130</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SAG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-24T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>185. Your 380, November 15.<note n="1" xml:id="d210fn1">Not printed.</note> After
                    long discussion and consultation by cable with <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName> in London, it has
                    been decided to continue negotiations with Norway here. As soon as the Allies
                    and ourselves have agreed on the terms to be presented, the terms will be cabled
                    to you. Negotiations are going on here with <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_NF1">Nansen</persName>, and some progress being
                    made.</p>
                <p>For your confidential information, the Department thinks it would be desirable
                    for you in your discussions of the matter with Norwegians to lay stress on the
                    fact that we are acting with the Allies and frequently we are compelled to yield
                    to them and make terms more onerous on neutrals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
